<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-04T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-04T13:00:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51C39/365: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-04T14:00:00-04:00">May 4, 1935—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>27. Your telegram 24, April 30, noon.<note n="38" xml:id="d581fn38">Not
                                printed.</note> You may in your discretion, and without expressing
                            an opinion concerning any proposal, express informally to the Minister
                            of Foreign Affairs the hope that the present negotiations may lead to an
                            agreement satisfactory to both parties.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>